WEBVTT

00:07.734 --> 00:10.934
YOU KNOW, I'VE SEEN CHERYL
DO THIS BEFORE.

00:11.000 --> 00:13.901
SHE JUST PRESSES A BUTTON...

00:13.968 --> 00:17.367
AND THE WHOLE THING
COLLAPSES.

00:19.000 --> 00:25.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:29.234 --> 00:31.334
THAT'S A BRAKE.

00:47.834 --> 00:49.300
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT!

00:49.367 --> 00:50.834
I THINK I HEARD A CLICK.

00:50.901 --> 00:52.934
THAT WAS MY KNEE.

01:10.501 --> 01:11.567
YOU WANT TO GET THE DOOR?

01:27.868 --> 01:29.667
HAH!

01:29.734 --> 01:32.067
OH, BABY.

01:37.934 --> 01:41.033
WHAT...HAS HAPPENED
TO AMERICA?

01:41.100 --> 01:43.634
IT'S GOING TO HELL
IN A HANDBASKET, JIM.

01:43.701 --> 01:45.067
BINGO!

01:45.133 --> 01:47.033
* B-I-N-G-O *

01:47.100 --> 01:49.067
* B-I-N-G-O *

01:49.133 --> 01:51.167
NO, NO, NO, GIRLS,
THAT'S OKAY.

01:51.234 --> 01:52.434
YOU KNOW WHAT? NOT NOW,

01:52.501 --> 01:54.634
BUT MOMMY WILL SING IT LATER
FOR YOU AS MUCH AS YOU WANT!

01:54.701 --> 01:56.901
YAY!

01:56.968 --> 01:59.000
I'M SITTING THERE WATCHING
THE DIRECTOR'S CUT

01:59.067 --> 02:00.601
OF "RED HEAT,"
WHICH, BY THE WAY, CHERYL,

02:00.667 --> 02:02.901
IS VERY GOOD.

02:02.968 --> 02:05.734
COMPLETELY OVERLOOKED
BY THE ACADEMY.

02:05.801 --> 02:09.601
ANYWAY, THE DVD PLAYER BREAKS
DOWN AND CRAPS RIGHT OUT ON ME.

02:09.667 --> 02:11.434
WHAT? WE'VE ONLY
HAD IT A WEEK!
BINGO!

02:11.501 --> 02:12.434
* B-I -- *

02:12.501 --> 02:14.801
AH-AH!

02:14.868 --> 02:15.868
THANK YOU.

02:15.934 --> 02:19.067
SO, I'M GONNA TAKE THIS BACK
TO LAZY AL'S,

02:19.133 --> 02:20.634
AND I'M GONNA EXCHANGE IT
AND GET A NEW ONE.

02:20.701 --> 02:22.133
BUT I NEED THAT RECEIPT.

02:23.868 --> 02:25.634
OH, JEEZ!

02:25.701 --> 02:26.667
OW.

02:26.734 --> 02:28.100
MY BINKY!

02:28.167 --> 02:29.701
MY WHISTLE!

02:29.767 --> 02:31.300
[ WHISTLE BLOWING ]

02:31.367 --> 02:33.467
THANKS, JIM. THAT'S WHERE
I KEEP ALL THE STUFF

02:33.534 --> 02:34.901
I DON'T WANT THEM
TO HAVE ANYMORE.

02:34.968 --> 02:36.667
MY NUDIE PEN.

02:38.734 --> 02:41.601
HELLO, INGRID.

02:41.667 --> 02:43.801
SHE LIVES IN A PEN, JIM.

02:49.968 --> 02:53.634
IF SHE WAS 5 FEET TALLER,
YOU'D BE GONE.

02:57.067 --> 03:00.601
HONEY, I GOTTA FIND
THAT RECEIPT.

03:00.667 --> 03:01.968
I KNOW I PUT THAT RECEIPT
IN HERE.

03:02.033 --> 03:03.067
WHAT DID YOU DO WITH IT?

03:03.133 --> 03:05.234
ME?! I NEVER TAKE ANYTHING
OUT OF THAT DRAWER.

03:05.300 --> 03:07.334
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO'S ALWAYS LOSING THINGS,

03:07.400 --> 03:08.734
LIKE OUR HONEYMOON TICKETS.

03:08.801 --> 03:10.000
I DID NOT LOSE THOSE TICKETS.

03:10.067 --> 03:12.501
YOU TOLD ME TO PUT THEM
IN THE GREEN SUITCASE.

03:12.567 --> 03:13.901
WE DIDN'T TAKE
THE GREEN SUITCASE.

03:13.968 --> 03:15.834
WELL, WHY DID YOU TELL ME
TO PUT 'EM IN THE GREEN
SUITCASE?

03:15.901 --> 03:17.601
WHY WOULD I TELL YOU
TO PUT THEM IN A SUITCASE
YOU WEREN'T EVEN TAKING?

03:17.667 --> 03:20.467
CHERYL, ONLY YOU
CAN ANSWER THAT.

03:22.133 --> 03:23.968
BESIDES,
THAT WAS 10 YEARS AGO.

03:24.033 --> 03:26.901
CAN'T YOU THINK OF ANYTHING
RECENTLY THAT I LOST?

03:26.968 --> 03:28.667
UH, 10 POUNDS?

03:28.734 --> 03:31.334
ALTHOUGH, IN YOUR DEFENSE,
YOU DID FIND THEM.

03:34.133 --> 03:38.067
THAT IS A CHEAP SHOT, CHERYL.
I AM STORING THAT ONE.

03:38.133 --> 03:41.801
AW, YOU MEAN WHERE
YOUR HAIR USED TO BE?

03:41.868 --> 03:44.868
WHAT?!

03:44.934 --> 03:48.200
DID I FORGET A BIRTHDAY
OR SOMETHING?
WHAT'S GOIN' ON HERE?

03:48.267 --> 03:50.033
NO, NO, I'M JUST SICK
OF YOU LOSING THINGS
ALL THE TIME

03:50.100 --> 03:51.367
AND BLAMING ME.
LIKE, LIKE --

03:51.434 --> 03:54.734
LIKE MY CAR KEYS
OR YOUR SUNGLASSES
OR THE ELECTRIC BILL.

03:54.801 --> 03:57.968
COME ON, CHERYL, THAT WAS FUN.
IT WAS LIKE CAMPING.

03:58.033 --> 03:59.501
BESIDES, YOU KNOW WHAT?

03:59.567 --> 04:02.133
YOU GOTTA STOP
KEEPING SCORE WITH ME.

04:02.200 --> 04:04.968
YOU STORE THESE LISTS
IN YOUR HEAD.

04:05.033 --> 04:07.567
OH, YOU MEAN UP HERE
WITH MY THICK,
LUSTROUS HAIR?

04:10.000 --> 04:11.367
CHERYL...

04:14.200 --> 04:16.500
YOU ARE MAKING ME
VERY ANGRY.

04:16.567 --> 04:17.934
AND VERY HOT.

04:19.701 --> 04:20.767
NOW, COME ON.

04:20.834 --> 04:23.434
IT'S OBVIOUS THAT SOMEONE
JUST BROKE IN HERE

04:23.501 --> 04:25.868
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT
AND STOLE MY RECEIPT!

04:25.934 --> 04:27.434
YEAH, JIM.

04:27.501 --> 04:29.334
IT'S PROBABLY HALFWAY
TO SOUTH AMERICA BY NOW,

04:29.400 --> 04:31.734
CHOPPED UP
AND SOLD FOR CONFETTI.

04:31.801 --> 04:34.868
[ SIGHS ]
I KNOW IT'S IN HERE!

04:34.934 --> 04:36.300
HONEY, SERIOUSLY,
YOU PROBABLY DON'T
WANT TO TOUCH ANYTHING

04:36.367 --> 04:38.901
'CAUSE THE POLICE ARE
GONNA WANT TO DUST
FOR PRINTS.

04:40.133 --> 04:41.067
I'M GONNA KICK YOUR ASS!

04:41.133 --> 04:42.834
AAH! [ LAUGHS ]

04:47.868 --> 04:51.400
AH, TIFFANY...

04:51.467 --> 04:54.300
THAT WICKED LADY
TOOK YOUR SISTER AWAY.

04:59.868 --> 05:01.000
HI, WELCOME TO LAZY AL'S,

05:01.067 --> 05:03.968
WHERE WE'RE TOO DARN LAZY
TO RAISE OUR PRICES.

05:04.033 --> 05:06.968
I BET YOU HATE SAYING
THAT, DON'T YOU?

05:07.033 --> 05:09.601
NO, I DON'T.

05:13.601 --> 05:15.400
WELL, THIS THING
IS BROKEN HERE,

05:15.467 --> 05:17.767
AND I WANT TO EXCHANGE IT
FOR A NEW ONE.

05:17.834 --> 05:18.767
OKAY. CAN I SEE
A RECEIPT?

05:18.834 --> 05:22.901
WELL, MY, UH --
MY WIFE LOST IT.

05:22.968 --> 05:24.467
WOMEN, HUH?

05:27.467 --> 05:28.567
DON'T GET ME STARTED.

05:28.634 --> 05:29.634
YEAH.

05:31.801 --> 05:34.033
NO RETURNS
WITHOUT A RECEIPT.
NO EXCEPTIONS.

05:34.100 --> 05:35.234
AW, COME ON, BUDDY.

05:35.300 --> 05:37.367
WE ALL KNOW THAT RULES
ARE MEANT TO BE BROKEN, HUH?

05:37.434 --> 05:38.667
[ SIGHS ]

05:48.701 --> 05:51.200
ARE YOU TRYING TO BRIBE ME
WITH AN ARBY'S COUPON?

05:53.267 --> 05:57.300
OKAY, I UNDERSTAND.
YOU'RE A WORTHY OPPONENT.

05:57.367 --> 06:00.934
LET'S MAKE THIS
A, UH, GAME OF SKILL.

06:02.434 --> 06:04.434
I'M THINKING OF A NUMBER
BETWEEN ONE AND 10.

06:04.501 --> 06:05.868
SEVEN.

06:05.934 --> 06:07.467
DAMN!

06:09.434 --> 06:10.868
I NEED THAT RECEIPT,
SIR.

06:10.934 --> 06:12.534
I'M THINKING
OF A NUMBER--
63.

06:12.601 --> 06:13.868
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

06:30.767 --> 06:32.501
WELL, WELL, WELL.

06:33.801 --> 06:36.300
OH, GEE.

06:36.367 --> 06:39.267
WHAT'S THAT, JIM,
THE NEW DVD PLAYER?

06:39.334 --> 06:42.133
WHY, YES, MY DARLING,
IT IS.

06:42.200 --> 06:44.400
OH, JIM, YOU'RE MY HERO.

06:44.467 --> 06:46.501
WOULD YOU LIKE STEAK-UMS
FOR LUNCH

06:46.567 --> 06:50.868
FOLLOWED BY
AFTERNOON SEX?

06:50.934 --> 06:54.000
WELL, YOU KNOW, CHERYL,
I REALLY DIDN'T THINK
ABOUT THAT,

06:54.067 --> 06:56.067
BUT YES, I WOULD!

06:56.133 --> 06:59.934
OKAY. OKAY, I GET IT.
YOU DIDN'T LOSE THE RECEIPT.

07:00.000 --> 07:01.467
OH, I DIDN'T LOSE
THE RECEIPT.

07:01.534 --> 07:02.701
THAT'S VERY INTERESTING.

07:02.767 --> 07:04.734
SO MAYBE
YOU WERE INCORRECT?

07:04.801 --> 07:06.634
MAYBE YOU COULD'VE BEEN
POSSIBLY WRONG,

07:06.701 --> 07:09.167
PERCHANCE MISTAKEN?

07:09.234 --> 07:11.567
ALL RIGHT!
I GOT IT!

07:11.634 --> 07:12.801
ALL RIGHT.

07:12.868 --> 07:14.734
CHERYL, EXCUSE ME.

07:14.801 --> 07:16.501
I AM GONNA TAKE A NAP...

07:17.667 --> 07:20.767
...TO SAVE UP ENERGY
FOR OUR AFTERNOON SEX.

07:20.834 --> 07:23.868
OKAY, HONEY.

07:23.934 --> 07:25.767
YOU WIN.
ENJOY YOUR NAP.

07:25.834 --> 07:27.267
THANK YOU.

07:27.334 --> 07:28.534
BINGO!

07:28.601 --> 07:31.868
* B-I-N-G-O, B-I-N-G-O *

07:31.934 --> 07:35.033
* B-I-N-G-O,
AND BINGO WAS HIS NAME-O *

07:37.834 --> 07:40.601
[ INSTRUMENTS TUNING ]

07:40.667 --> 07:43.434
BOYS, I AM A GENIUS.

07:43.501 --> 07:44.801
YEAH? SPELL IT.

07:44.868 --> 07:47.467
YEAH, GO AHEAD
AND MAKE FUN OF ME.

07:47.534 --> 07:50.133
BUT I JUST FOOLED MY WIFE,
AND SHE'S A VERY SMART LADY.

07:50.200 --> 07:51.667
ALL RIGHT.
SO, HOW DID YOU FOOL HER?

07:51.734 --> 07:54.467
YOU SEE, I WAS GONNA RETURN
THIS BROKEN DVD PLAYER.

07:54.534 --> 07:55.501
RIGHT?
OKAY.

07:55.567 --> 07:56.634
BUT I NEEDED THE RECEIPT

07:56.701 --> 07:57.701
AND I COULDN'T FIND IT,

07:57.767 --> 08:00.000
AND CHERYL ACCUSED ME
OF LOSING IT.

08:00.067 --> 08:01.033
DID YOU?

08:01.100 --> 08:03.467
WELL, YEAH,
PRETTY MUCH.

08:03.534 --> 08:07.167
BUT THAT'S WHY I WENT OUT
AND BOUGHT A NEW DVD PLAYER

08:07.234 --> 08:09.801
SO SHE WOULDN'T, YOU KNOW,
HARP ON ME FOR 50 YEARS

08:09.868 --> 08:11.567
ABOUT THE MISTAKES I MADE.

08:11.634 --> 08:13.200
YEAH, I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

08:13.267 --> 08:14.834
CHERYL STILL WON'T LET ME
FORGET THE TIME

08:14.901 --> 08:16.300
WHEN I USED HER EASY-BAKE OVEN

08:16.367 --> 08:19.200
TO CREMATE MY DEAD FROG,
MR. HOPPERS.

08:20.367 --> 08:22.200
WELL, GUYS, WOMEN.

08:22.267 --> 08:25.400
WOMEN ARE LIKE A DOG
WITH A BONE.

08:25.467 --> 08:27.033
THEY BURY IT
FOR A WHILE,

08:27.100 --> 08:30.534
AND THEN THEY DIG IT UP
WHEN THEY WANT TO USE IT
AGAINST YOU.

08:30.601 --> 08:32.167
MY BARBER TOLD ME THAT.

08:32.234 --> 08:34.467
YOU WERE IN THE CHAIR
LONG ENOUGH
TO GET ALL THAT?

08:34.534 --> 08:35.501
[ RIMSHOT ]

08:35.567 --> 08:37.200
HA HA HA! I LOVE IT!

08:37.267 --> 08:38.400
YEAH, YEAH.

08:38.467 --> 08:41.967
ALL RIGHT.
1, 2, 3, 4!

08:42.033 --> 08:44.601
[ BLUES MUSIC PLAYING ]

08:44.667 --> 08:46.334
[ BLOWING WHISTLE
RHYTHMICALLY ]

08:46.400 --> 08:48.000
WHOO!
WHO'S GOT THE MAGIC?

08:48.067 --> 08:49.400
MOM'S GOT THE MAGIC.

08:49.467 --> 08:50.868
OH, YEAH.

08:52.067 --> 08:54.067
I AM NOT SPEAKING
TO YOU,

08:54.133 --> 08:55.501
AND DON'T ACT LIKE
YOU DON'T KNOW WHY.

08:55.567 --> 08:56.701
OKAY.

08:56.767 --> 08:58.534
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

08:58.601 --> 09:00.000
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT YOU DID, DO YOU?

09:00.067 --> 09:01.534
UH, OVERREACTED
TO SOMETHING SMALL?

09:01.601 --> 09:03.033
OH, SORRY.
THAT'S WHAT YOU DO.

09:05.167 --> 09:06.434
I HATE YOU WHEN YOU DANCE.

09:09.000 --> 09:11.367
STOP DANCING!

09:11.434 --> 09:13.734
I MADE YOUR STUPID
SPAGHETTI SAUCE
LAST NIGHT FOR MY DATE,

09:13.801 --> 09:14.767
AND IT WAS AWFUL.

09:14.834 --> 09:17.200
OH, HONEY, YOUR DATES
ARE ALWAYS AWFUL.

09:19.133 --> 09:20.701
OKAY, WHAT DID
YOU DO WRONG?

09:20.767 --> 09:22.167
I DIDN'T DO
ANYTHING WRONG.

09:22.234 --> 09:24.434
I FOLLOWED YOUR RECIPE
EXACTLY.

09:24.501 --> 09:27.701
"ONE CAN OF TOMATO PASTE,
3 TABLESPOONS OF OLIVE OIL,

09:27.767 --> 09:28.901
ONE TABLESPOON
OF ORANGES" --

09:28.968 --> 09:30.000
OREGANO!

09:33.000 --> 09:37.234
NOT ORANGES!
YOU'RE NOT MAKING A SMOOTHIE!

09:37.300 --> 09:40.634
OH, MY GOD. LAZY AL'S.

09:40.701 --> 09:42.701
THIS IS THE RECEIPT
FOR THE DVD PLAYER.

09:45.100 --> 09:48.434
JIM DID LOSE THE RECEIPT.
HE IS SO BUSTED!

09:48.501 --> 09:49.501
WHERE'D YOU GET THIS?

09:49.567 --> 09:51.634
FROM YOU. YOU TOOK IT
OUT OF THAT DRAWER,

09:51.701 --> 09:54.334
WROTE THE RECIPE ON IT,
AND HANDED IT TO ME.

09:56.634 --> 09:58.334
YOU ARE LYING.

10:03.334 --> 10:04.334
Cheryl: OH, MAN!

10:04.400 --> 10:06.701
JIM WAS RIGHT.
I DID LOSE THE RECEIPT.

10:06.767 --> 10:09.234
WAIT A MINUTE.
IF HE DIDN'T HAVE THE RECEIPT,

10:09.300 --> 10:12.067
HOW DID HE GET LAZY AL
TO TAKE HIS DVD PLAYER BACK?

10:12.133 --> 10:14.834
MAYBE HE UNDID
HIS TOP BUTTON
AND CRIED.

10:16.234 --> 10:18.400
I ONCE RETURNED
A CAR LIKE THAT.

10:19.200 --> 10:20.734
HE TOTALLY DECEIVED ME.

10:20.801 --> 10:23.000
WELL, CHERYL, WHAT HAVE
I BEEN TELLING YOU
FOR 10 YEARS?

10:23.067 --> 10:26.100
THAT MAN
HAS NO GOOD QUALITIES.

10:26.167 --> 10:27.567
COME ON.
LET'S GO NAIL HIM.

10:27.634 --> 10:29.934
I CAN'T.
WHY?!

10:30.000 --> 10:32.234
BECAUSE HE'LL KNOW THAT I KNOW
THAT HE DIDN'T LOSE THE RECEIPT,

10:32.300 --> 10:33.400
AND HE'LL SAY,
"HOW DO YOU KNOW?"

10:33.467 --> 10:34.834
AND I'LL SAY,
"BECAUSE I GAVE IT TO DANA,"

10:34.901 --> 10:36.300
AND HE'LL SAY, "SO IT WAS REALLY
YOU WHO LOST THE RECEIPT."

10:36.367 --> 10:38.467
AND I WON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO SAY.

10:40.067 --> 10:41.400
WOW.

10:41.467 --> 10:45.634
I MUST HAVE NO LIFE,
BECAUSE I FIND THIS
FASCINATING.

10:45.701 --> 10:47.400
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

10:47.467 --> 10:50.701
OH. LISTEN CAREFULLY,
LITTLE SISTER.

10:50.767 --> 10:54.267
MEN ARE LIKE A DOG
WITH A BONE.

10:54.334 --> 10:57.067
THEY'LL BURY IT
FOR A WHILE,

10:57.133 --> 10:58.734
BUT THEY'LL DIG IT UP
WHEN THEY NEED TO.

11:00.167 --> 11:02.734
ALSO, THERE'S THE CHEWING
AND THE LICKING, BUT...

11:04.267 --> 11:06.100
ALL RIGHT. HANG ON.

11:06.167 --> 11:07.501
WHAT'S THAT?

11:07.567 --> 11:09.167
THEY'RE TRYING
TO GET ME
FOR JURY DUTY.

11:09.234 --> 11:11.234
UHH!

11:11.300 --> 11:13.267
BYE, GUYS.
SEE YA.

11:15.801 --> 11:17.267
WATCH THE DOOR.

11:17.334 --> 11:20.067
OKAY.
WHAT AM I LOOKING FOR?

11:20.133 --> 11:21.601
IF YOU SEE CHERYL,
SAY SOMETHING.

11:21.667 --> 11:23.434
LIKE WHAT?

11:23.501 --> 11:27.801
LIKE, "HEY, JIM,
CHERYL'S COMING."

11:27.868 --> 11:30.033
SEEMS A LITTLE LONG.

11:30.100 --> 11:32.601
HOW ABOUT "BLUE CANARY"?

11:32.667 --> 11:34.534
JUST WATCH
THE DAMN DOOR!

11:35.968 --> 11:38.167
BLUE CANARY!

11:43.501 --> 11:46.501
NO. NO, REALLY,
IT'S A BLUE CANARY.

11:49.667 --> 11:51.567
WHAT ARE THE ODDS?

11:54.067 --> 11:55.534
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:55.601 --> 11:58.567
I AM RETURNING
THIS BROKEN DVD PLAYER.

11:58.634 --> 12:00.601
I THOUGHT THEY WOULDN'T TAKE IT
WITHOUT A RECEIPT.

12:00.667 --> 12:04.367
OH, I HAVE A RECEIPT...
FROM THE NEW DVD PLAYER.

12:04.434 --> 12:07.467
THAT'S JUST WRONG.

12:07.534 --> 12:09.033
HOW DO YOU SLEEP
AT NIGHT?

12:09.100 --> 12:10.934
IN THE NUDE--
WITH YOUR SISTER.

12:14.901 --> 12:15.934
Jim: OKAY, OKAY.

12:16.000 --> 12:17.567
ALL WE'RE GONNA DO
IS WE'RE GONNA GO IN THERE,

12:17.634 --> 12:19.767
WE'RE GONNA GET OUR MONEY,
AND THEN WE'RE GONNA GET OUT.

12:19.834 --> 12:22.234
SO BE CALM.

12:22.300 --> 12:23.968
[ SCOFFS ]
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

12:24.033 --> 12:26.567
WHAT'S THAT IN MY VEINS?
OH, IT'S ICE WATER.

12:28.033 --> 12:29.734
OKAY, MR. ICEMAN.

12:32.400 --> 12:34.200
STAY CLOSE.

12:34.267 --> 12:35.234
HEY.

12:35.300 --> 12:36.501
HI, WELCOME
TO LAZY AL'S,

12:36.567 --> 12:39.400
WHERE WE'RE
TOO DARN LAZY
TO RAISE OUR PRI--

12:39.467 --> 12:43.234
SWEET MOTHER OF GOD!
WE'RE LOCKED IN!

12:43.300 --> 12:46.167
IT OPENS IN, SIR.
JUST PULL IT.

12:46.234 --> 12:47.701
Oh. Sorry.

12:58.601 --> 13:02.100
I WANTED TO RETURN THIS
FOR CASH.

13:02.167 --> 13:03.567
OKAY. CAN I SEE
YOUR RECEIPT?

13:03.634 --> 13:07.133
OH. OH, I THINK
I CAN SCARE ONE UP.

13:12.167 --> 13:16.968
OKAY.
THERE'S A PROBLEM.

13:17.033 --> 13:20.434
ASIDE FROM
THIS FROZEN TATER TOT...

13:22.701 --> 13:26.234
THE SERIAL NUMBERS
ON THIS DVD PLAYER
AND THIS RECEIPT

13:26.300 --> 13:27.434
DON'T MATCH.

13:27.501 --> 13:29.601
WHAT HAPPENED TO
"THE CUSTOMER IS ALWAYS RIGHT"?

13:29.667 --> 13:33.534
THAT GOES OUT THE WINDOW
WHEN THEY'RE TRYING
TO RIP US OFF.

13:33.601 --> 13:35.801
ALL RIGHT, I'M GONNA
CALL MY LAWYER, SIR.

13:35.868 --> 13:37.667
[ PUNCHING KEYS ]

13:37.734 --> 13:40.567
ONE SECOND, PLEASE.

13:42.567 --> 13:43.934
YES, I'LL HOLD.

13:47.767 --> 13:50.601
YES, JOHNNIE COCHRAN, PLEASE.

13:50.667 --> 13:52.167
SIR, THAT'S
A PRICE SCANNER.

14:02.667 --> 14:05.601
IF YOU WALK OUT RIGHT NOW,
I WON'T CALL THE POLICE.

14:10.133 --> 14:11.534
[ BANGING ]

14:11.601 --> 14:13.033
IT OPENS IN, SIR.

14:22.133 --> 14:23.167
HEY.

14:27.634 --> 14:30.400
BLUE...CANARY.

14:34.000 --> 14:35.801
SO, WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
DOING?

14:35.868 --> 14:37.968
WELL, WE WERE JUST, UM...

14:38.033 --> 14:39.601
T-TALKING MAN STUFF.

14:39.667 --> 14:40.934
YEAH, YOU KNOW, WE'RE --

14:41.000 --> 14:43.868
I WAS GONNA DO
SOME MEASURING AND STUFF.

14:43.934 --> 14:44.968
I WAS THINKING MAYBE --
I DON'T KNOW --

14:45.067 --> 14:49.934
CHANGE THE GARAGE
INTO A...STUDY FOR MY BOOKS.

14:50.000 --> 14:52.968
WHY? IS THE RACK
NEXT TO THE TOILET
GETTING TOO SMALL?

14:54.734 --> 14:56.534
WHAT'S THIS?

14:56.601 --> 14:57.801
OH, UH...

14:57.868 --> 15:00.334
WELL, THAT'S THE DVD PLAYER.

15:00.400 --> 15:03.133
OH. REALLY?
NOW, THAT'S FUNNY,

15:03.200 --> 15:04.434
'CAUSE THE GIRLS
ARE IN THE HOUSE

15:04.501 --> 15:06.167
WATCHING A DVD
RIGHT NOW.

15:11.901 --> 15:14.234
SO... YOU WANNA TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON?

15:16.334 --> 15:17.834
DANA...

15:17.901 --> 15:19.167
WHAT? OH, COME ON!

15:19.234 --> 15:21.067
THIS IS THE ONLY REASON
I REALLY COME OVER HERE.

15:21.133 --> 15:22.968
YOU THINK I LIKE
TO WATCH HIM EAT?!

15:28.868 --> 15:30.934
ALL RIGHT.
SO, WHAT'S GOING ON?

15:31.000 --> 15:33.167
WELL, UH, YOU KNOW.

15:34.834 --> 15:38.267
LONG STORY SHORT --

15:38.334 --> 15:39.534
AND HERE WE ARE.

15:40.834 --> 15:44.400
YEAH, SO YOU WANT TO GIVE ME
THE SLIGHTLY LONGER VERSION?

15:44.467 --> 15:48.801
SURE. I LOST THE RECEIPT
AND BOUGHT A NEW DVD PLAYER,
AND HERE WE ARE.

15:48.868 --> 15:51.434
OH, MAN! YOU ARE
UNBELIEVABLE!

15:51.501 --> 15:53.400
ALL RIGHT.

15:53.467 --> 15:57.300
I'M STANDING IN FRONT OF
YOU, TOTALLY VULNERABLE.

15:57.367 --> 15:59.968
IF YOU WANT ME TO TAKE
MY PANTS OFF, I WILL.

16:03.834 --> 16:06.367
WHY WOULD I WANT YOU
TO TAKE YOUR PANTS OFF?

16:06.434 --> 16:09.701
JUST AN EXPRESSION.

16:09.767 --> 16:11.400
COME ON.
COME ON, CHERYL.

16:11.467 --> 16:12.901
GIVE IT TO ME,
BOTH BARRELS.

16:12.968 --> 16:14.601
I'M GOING TO!
ALL RIGHT.

16:14.667 --> 16:17.968
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.
I'M NOT PULLING ANY PUNCHES.

16:18.033 --> 16:18.968
I KNOW. I KNOW.

16:19.033 --> 16:22.234
ALL RIGHT.
OH, DAMN IT!

16:22.300 --> 16:26.934
PERFECT OPPORTUNITY TO BUST YOU,
AND I CAN'T DO IT.

16:27.000 --> 16:28.267
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

16:28.334 --> 16:29.334
OH!

16:29.400 --> 16:31.300
I TOOK THE RECEIPT
OUT OF THE DRAWER.

16:31.367 --> 16:34.067
I WROTE A RECIPE ON IT,
AND I HANDED IT TO DANA.

16:34.133 --> 16:38.100
[ SIGHS ]

16:38.167 --> 16:40.701
WHOA!

16:40.767 --> 16:42.234
JIM.

16:42.300 --> 16:45.634
DON'T...PLEASE!

16:48.300 --> 16:53.734
I CAN'T EVEN LOOK
AT YOU RIGHT NOW.

16:53.801 --> 16:55.834
COME ON!
WE BOTH LIED.

16:55.901 --> 16:59.067
OH, DON'T DRAG ME
INTO YOUR WEB OF DECEIT.

16:59.133 --> 17:02.934
WAIT!
YOU GOT THE RECEIPT.
I CAN RETURN THE DVD.

17:03.000 --> 17:06.133
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.
HERE'S WHERE MY STORY
GETS FUNNY.

17:06.200 --> 17:09.733
AHH...
I BURNED IT.

17:09.800 --> 17:11.534
WHY?

17:11.601 --> 17:14.300
WELL, BECAUSE I KNEW
THAT SOONER OR LATER
YOU'D FIND IT,

17:14.367 --> 17:16.032
AND THEN YOU'D JUST
LORD IT OVER ME.

17:16.099 --> 17:17.867
WELL, I BOUGHT
A NEW DVD PLAYER

17:17.934 --> 17:19.834
BECAUSE I DIDN'T WANT
YOU TO LORD IT OVER ME

17:19.901 --> 17:21.032
AND THEN PUT IT
ON THAT LIST OF YOURS.

17:21.099 --> 17:22.233
OH, MAN!

17:22.300 --> 17:24.166
THE AMOUNT OF TIME
WE SPEND KEEPING SCORE,

17:24.233 --> 17:25.601
IT'S JUST EXHAUSTING.

17:25.666 --> 17:28.300
IT IS.
OHH!

17:28.367 --> 17:32.067
CHERYL...
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE?

17:32.133 --> 17:35.667
I MEAN, WE -- KEEPING
LISTS ON EACH OTHER.

17:35.734 --> 17:38.267
I MEAN, THERE'S GOTTA BE
SOME GOOD THINGS
ON THAT LIST,

17:38.334 --> 17:39.901
OR WE WOULDN'T
BE MARRIED
ALL THESE YEARS.

17:39.968 --> 17:41.100
I'VE GOT GOOD THINGS
ON THE LIST.

17:41.167 --> 17:42.400
REALLY?
YEAH.

17:42.467 --> 17:43.567
WHAT?

17:43.634 --> 17:46.801
OH, HERE'S ONE.
"WILL EAT ANYTHING."

17:48.467 --> 17:50.901
HOW ABOUT A GOOD THING
THAT'S NOT INSULTING, TOO.

17:50.968 --> 17:53.200
OH, OKAY.
OH, I KNOW!

17:53.267 --> 17:54.400
OH, NO. NO.

17:54.467 --> 17:56.901
OH! OH!
OH, NO.

17:56.968 --> 17:59.601
CHERYL, COME ON!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
TO ME HERE?

17:59.667 --> 18:01.133
OH, OKAY.

18:01.200 --> 18:06.100
OKAY, WELL, I WAS KINDA
SAVING THIS ONE, BUT, UM...

18:06.167 --> 18:09.400
HE WAS A GOOD FATHER AND
A LOVING, DEVOTED HUSBAND.

18:09.467 --> 18:11.267
"WAS"?

18:11.334 --> 18:13.968
IT'S MY WIDOW'S LIST.

18:14.033 --> 18:16.467
IT'S THE KIND OF STUFF
I WAS SAVING FOR YOUR FUNERAL.

18:17.834 --> 18:20.133
YOU THINK YOU'RE GONNA
LIVE LONGER THAN ME?

18:20.200 --> 18:22.868
JIM, YOU ORDER A SIDE OF EGGS
WITH YOUR OMELET!

18:26.000 --> 18:28.033
OKAY. HERE GOES.

18:28.100 --> 18:31.834
[ FUNERAL DIRGE PLAYS ]

18:31.901 --> 18:33.901
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

18:33.968 --> 18:35.834
I'D LIKE TO THANK YOU BOTH
FOR COMING.

18:35.901 --> 18:37.033
OH!

18:40.167 --> 18:42.334
CHERYL, I HAVE MORE
FRIENDS THAN THAT.

18:42.400 --> 18:44.133
DEAD!

18:46.100 --> 18:47.634
[ SIGHS ]

18:47.701 --> 18:48.934
SINCE WE WERE MARRIED,

18:49.000 --> 18:51.701
A DAY HASN'T GONE BY
THAT JIM HASN'T MADE ME LAUGH.

18:52.934 --> 18:54.701
EVEN IF IT WAS AT HIM
RATHER THAN WITH HIM.

18:54.767 --> 18:56.467
HEY!
UH-UH!

18:58.434 --> 19:00.634
OH, AND HE'S SUCH
A GOOD FATHER.

19:00.701 --> 19:03.801
LIKE ALL THE TIMES HE STAYED UP
ALL NIGHT WITH RUBY

19:03.868 --> 19:04.934
WHEN SHE WAS SICK.

19:05.000 --> 19:08.234
OR WHEN GRACIE DROPPED
HER TEDDY BEAR IN THE LAKE

19:08.300 --> 19:11.100
AND HE JUMPED IN
WITH ALL HIS CLOTHES ON
TO SAVE IT.

19:11.167 --> 19:13.133
YEAH, I REMEMBER THAT.

19:13.200 --> 19:16.434
A BRAND-NEW ROLL
OF LIFESAVERS RUINED.

19:16.501 --> 19:20.834
ANYWAY...

19:20.901 --> 19:23.868
BLANK AND I WOULD LIKE TO INVITE
YOU ALL UP TO OUR LAVISH ESTATE

19:23.934 --> 19:26.334
FOR CHAMPAGNE AND CAVIAR.

19:26.400 --> 19:27.834
WHO'S BLANK?

19:27.901 --> 19:29.067
MY BOYFRIEND.

19:29.133 --> 19:31.100
YEAH, HE'S THE CUTE DOCTOR

19:31.167 --> 19:34.334
WHO FOUGHT SO VALIANTLY
TO SAVE YOU.

19:34.400 --> 19:35.968
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:36.033 --> 19:38.033
YOU'RE TOO MUCH.

19:38.100 --> 19:40.334
WELL, LET ME ASK YOU
SOMETHING.

19:40.400 --> 19:42.000
DID HE KISS LIKE THIS?

19:42.067 --> 19:44.167
MMM. MMM.

19:44.234 --> 19:45.868
NO. NO, HE DIDN'T.

19:45.934 --> 19:48.667
ACTUALLY,
HE KISSED LIKE THIS.

19:50.334 --> 19:53.601
MMM. MMM.

19:53.667 --> 19:55.734
MMM!

19:55.801 --> 19:58.133
I'LL KILL HIM!

19:58.200 --> 20:02.300
BUT FIRST...THIS.

20:04.334 --> 20:07.934
[ Voice breaking ] I JUST LOOKED
EVERYWHERE FOR THAT RECEIPT,

20:08.000 --> 20:10.100
AND I JUST COULDN'T FIND IT.

20:10.167 --> 20:11.100
[ SNIFFLES ]

20:11.167 --> 20:14.033
OH, IT'S HOT IN HERE,
ISN'T IT?

20:23.968 --> 20:25.968
[ GIGGLES ]

20:26.033 --> 20:28.234
ANYWAY...

20:28.300 --> 20:32.901
SO, UM, IF I DON'T GET $200
BY TOMORROW MORNING,

20:32.968 --> 20:34.868
MY TWIN SISTER AND I
AREN'T GONNA BE ABLE TO PAY

20:34.934 --> 20:37.868
THE ENROLLMENT FEE
FOR THE LINGERIE CONTEST.

20:40.801 --> 20:42.033
YEAH. OKAY.

20:42.100 --> 20:43.467
OH, YEAH. YEAH. YEAH.

20:43.534 --> 20:45.234
YEAH. YEAH.

20:47.067 --> 20:48.200
HERE, HERE.

20:48.267 --> 20:49.634
AND HERE'S A UNIVERSAL
REMOTE ON THE HOUSE.

20:49.701 --> 20:50.767
JUST TAKE THAT.

20:50.834 --> 20:52.634
OH, THANK YOU.

20:58.334 --> 21:00.100
IT OPENS IN,
YOU KNOW.

21:01.634 --> 21:02.901
THANK YOU.

21:06.767 --> 21:08.200
GOTCHA!

